28 premium contributions, penalties and assessments consistent with section 1233.
29 Sec. 12. 26 MRSA §850-F, sub-§12 is enacted to read:
30 12. Liability of successor for delinquent premium contributions, penalties and
31 assessments. An individual or organization that acquires an employer's organization, trade
32 or business or a substantial part of the assets of that organization, trade or business is liable
33 to the department for any premium contributions, penalties and assessments unpaid by the
34 employer in the amount owed. The individual's or organization's liability under this
35 subsection may not exceed the reasonable value of the organization, trade or business or
36 assets acquired. Upon written request, the department shall provide the successor individual
37 or organization with information about the amount owed and other information as
38 determined necessary.
